            "answer_text": "I am assuming you were mostly referring to the verb \u201crecover\u201d in this question. In that exact sentence, the correct form to use would be \u201cI hope you will get recovered soon\u201d. However, this is not the form you would use in standard English. You would generally say \u201cI hope you recover soon\u201d More common ways to phrase the sentiment are: \u201dI hope you get well soon\u201d / \u201cGet well soon!\u201d \u201dI wish you a fast recovery\u201d \u201dWishing you well\u201d \u201dTake good care\u201d ",
